Some common infra failure happening (snippet taken from a sonic-swss pipeline run, but the core error message is the same):

```
+ ip netns list
+ uname -a
Linux sonic-test-workers-001G4F 5.15.0-1082-azure #91~20.04.1-Ubuntu SMP Tue Feb 25 03:23:03 UTC 2025 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux
+ sudo /sbin/ip link add Vrf1 type vrf table 1001
/agent/_work/_temp/7c2d0fe1-c9e4-489f-a057-cb73d5b204b0.sh: line 6: 24923 Killed                  sudo /sbin/ip link add Vrf1 type vrf table 1001
+ echo 'vrf command failed'
+ exit 1
vrf command failed
```
Kernel module build is being done for 5.15.0-1086.95~20.04.1, but the agents appear to be running 5.15.0-1082-azure. The agents might need to be updated/rebooted.
